1.4 Creating & setting custom theme


theme_viny_bright <- function(){
  
  library(ggthemes)
  
  ggthemes::theme_fivethirtyeight() %+replace%
  
  theme(
    axis.title = element_text(),
    
    axis.text = element_text(size = 13),
    
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
    
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    
    legend.background = element_rect(fill = NA),
    
    legend.key = element_rect(fill = NA),

    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                              size = 19,
                              face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, colour = "maroon")
      )
  
  }

theme_set(theme_viny_bright())

2.3.2 CNN Model

conv_image_model <- keras_model_sequential()

2.3.2.1 Define Model

conv_image_model %>% 
    layer_conv_2d(filters = 32, kernel_size = c(3,3), input_shape = c(28, 28, 1), activation = "relu") %>% 
    layer_max_pooling_2d(pool_size = c(2,2)) %>% 
    layer_conv_2d(filters = 32, kernel_size = c(3,3), activation = "relu") %>% 
    layer_max_pooling_2d(pool_size = c(2,2)) %>% 
    layer_flatten() %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 128, activation = "relu") %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 10, activation = "softmax")

2.3.2.2 Compile Model

conv_image_model %>% 
    compile(
        optimizer = "adam",
        loss = "categorical_crossentropy",
        metrics = "accuracy")

2.3.2.3 fit model

conv_image_model %>%
    fit(
        x = cnn_train_images,
        y = train_labels,
        epoch = 50,
        batch_size = 128,
        validation_split = .8,
        callbacks = callback_early_stopping(patience = 5)
        )

2.4.2 tokenizer

model_tokenizer <- text_tokenizer(num_words = 10000)

one_hot_train_text <- sequences_to_matrix(model_tokenizer, train_text, "binary")
one_hot_test_text <- sequences_to_matrix(model_tokenizer, test_text, "binary")
one_hot_train_text %>% dim()

2.4.3 Define Model

text_model <- keras_model_sequential()

  reached elapsed time limit
text_model %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 512, input_shape = ncol(one_hot_train_text), activation = "relu") %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 512, activation = "relu") %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 512, activation = "relu") %>%
    layer_dense(units = 1, activation = "sigmoid")

text_model %>% 
    compile(
        optimizer = "adam",
        loss = "binary_crossentropy",
        metrics = "accuracy"
        )

        )
